    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single below-required-level factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to the single ASTM F1717 configuration tested, bounding the extrapolation risk. All three primary QoIs satisfy both quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. Note: this package conforms to the Minimal profile; digital signature is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow and has not yet been applied.",
